</physical_entity>
.</p>
<p>

Dr. Mauldin has written two books, ten refereed papers and several technical reports on natural language, autonomous information agents, information retrieval and expert systems.  He is also one of the authors of <it><system wordnetid="104377057" confidence="0.8">
<artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<instrumentality wordnetid="103575240" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../939/287939.xml">
Rog-O-Matic</link></instrumentality>
</artifact>
</system>
</it> and <it>Julia</it> (a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../840/43840.xml">
Turing test</link> competitor in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../725/238725.xml">
Loebner Prize</link>).</p>
<p>

The Verbot program is based on Dr. Mauldin's early work in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../652/21652.xml">
natural language processing</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../349/148349.xml">
Chatterbot</link>s.</p>
<p>

Mauldin and his family are known as <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://lazytoad.com/teamtoad/index.html">
Team Toad</weblink> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../350/1657350.xml">
Robot Combat</link>, having competed at <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../839/172839.xml">
Battlebots</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../198/299198.xml">
NERC</link> and <event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<social_event wordnetid="107288639" confidence="0.8">
<contest wordnetid="107456188" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../729/6281729.xml">
RFL</link></psychological_feature>
</contest>
</social_event>
</event>
 events between 2000 and 2006.  Their robot Ice Cube is the 2006 RFL National Middleweight Champion.</p>

